        "timestamp": "2017-08-30 00:13:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(6 comments)\n\nAll replacements of catch(Throwable t) to catch(Exception t) should be changed to catch(Exception e). \n\nBut as far as catching generic Exception, I think these should all be narrowed but this seems to be endemic in the code, so I'll leave to others.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "af11984b37c3daa2560f1e90647fcde3644aaf71",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 667,
          "name": "Marcus Williams",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "marcus.williams@intel.com",
          "username": "mgkwill"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-08-30 00:20:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nP.S. if you look at sonar for this blocker, it mentions compliant solutions and they do not include generic exception catching: \"Compliant Solution\n\ntry { /* ... */ } catch (RuntimeException e) { /* ... */ }\ntry { /* ... */ } catch (MyException e) { /* ... */ }\"",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
